author: Minyvonne Burke
title: New Jersey coronavirus cases top 81,000
description: "We will do everything in our power to stop the spread of this disease and lose fewer and fewer residents to it," Gov. Phil Murphy said.
content:
More than 81,000 people in New Jersey have tested positive for COVID-19, Gov. Phil Murphy said at his daily news conference Saturday. 
Murphy said in the last 24 hours more than 3,000 residents have tested positive for the virus, bringing the total to 81,420… [+5971 chars]
